# OpenAI API Configuration has been removed
# Quiz generation now uses local mock data

# Google Sheets API Configuration (Optional - for data storage)
# If not provided, the app will use local storage for development
GOOGLE_CLIENT_EMAIL=your_google_service_account_email@project.iam.gserviceaccount.com
GOOGLE_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\nYour private key here\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n"
GOOGLE_SHEET_ID=your_google_sheet_id_here

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local
# 2. Replace the placeholder values with your actual API keys
# 3. OpenAI API key is no longer required
# 4. For Google Sheets API: Create a service account at https://console.cloud.google.com/
#    - Enable Google Sheets API
#    - Create credentials (Service Account)
#    - Download the JSON key file
#    - Use the client_email and private_key from the JSON file
#    - Create a Google Sheet and share it with the service account email
#    - Copy the sheet ID from the URL